---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Homepage"
  description="Portfolio of Sara Ringkow Petersen"
  ogtitle="SRP portfolio - homepage"
  ogdescription="Portfolio-site for Sara Ringkow Petersen"
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <div id="cursor"></div>
  <section id="hero" class="relative container md:max-w-3xl max-w-md mx-auto md:text-left text-center py-16">
    <!-- Content of Hero Section (kept on top with z-index) -->
    <div class="relative z-10">
      <h1 id="hero-title" class="font-bold text-[#fafafa] tracking-wider md:pt-52 pt-60">Hey there!</h1>
      <h2 id="hero-subtitle" class="font-medium text-[#fafafa] mt-4 mb-12 tracking-widest">Welcome to my portfolio</h2>
      <p id="hero-text" class="text-gray-300 mt-6 leading-7 mx-auto md:text-lg text-base">
        Hi! <br class="md:hidden block" /> I'm Sara Ringkow Petersen, an aspiring multimedia-designer with a strong passion for creating engaging and accessible
        digital experiences. Further down the page, you can read a bit about who I am, look through some of my projects&mdash; highlighted or not &mdash;or
        simply reach out if you have any questions or just want to say hi. <br /><br />Use the navigation menu to navigate around to the different
        sections or subpages, or click the button down below to go directly to my projects.
      </p>
      <div id="hero-button" class="button-container">
        <a
          href="#projects"
          class="relative z-10 text-[#fafafa] bg-site-red font-bold rounded-lg text-sm px-6 py-3 inline-flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden group mt-8 transition duration-300 uppercase hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-red-600/50 hover:bg-red-600"
        >
          <span class="button-text flex items-center gap-2 text-sm relative z-10 w-full text-center uppercase">
            View projects <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="1.5"
              stroke="currentColor"
              class="size-4"
            >
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 13.5 12 21m0 0-7.5-7.5M12 21V3"></path>
            </svg></span
          >
          <span
            class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-600 to-red-800 transition-all duration-500 ease-in-out translate-x-full group-hover:translate-x-0"
          ></span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!-- About Section -->
  <section id="about" class="container max-w-screen-xl mx-auto md:pt-24 pt-8 py-12 px-6">
    <div class="bg-gray-800 bg-opacity-70 p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center">
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 lg:pr-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#fafafa] md:text-left text-center">About me</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-300 leading-7 md:text-left text-center">
          As a multimedia-designer, I <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">specialise</span> in UX and web design, with a strong
          focus on <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">accessibility</span> and inclusive design. I have a deep understanding
          of the meaning of design, its impact on usability, and the overall importance of creating visually engaging and user-friendly interfaces. As
          someone who's <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">late-diagnosed</span>
          with autism, I know what it's like to be a person who's not fully capable of certain things and have limited understanding of the world around
          them. This has led me to my <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">main goal</span>&mdash; to create digital
          experiences that are accessible and inclusive for all users, regardless of their disabilities.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-300 leading-7 md:text-left text-center">
          <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">Creativity</span> is at the heart of everything I do, driving me to explore the
          world of design with enthusiasm and curiosity. Each project
          <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">presents a chance</span> to transform ideas into meaningful experiences. I thrive
          on the excitement of
          <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">experimenting with new techniques</span> and discovering innovative ways to bring
          concepts to life. As I journey through this ever-evolving field, I look forward to <span
            class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">embracing new challenges</span
          > and forging connections that <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">inspire</span> growth and creativity. The future
          holds endless possibilities, and I'm eager to see where this path will lead me.
        </p>
        <!-- Button Container -->
        <div class="flex md:justify-start justify-center w-full mt-8">
          <a
            href="/about_me"
            class="project-button relative z-10 text-[#fafafa] bg-site-red font-bold rounded-lg text-sm px-6 py-3 inline-flex overflow-hidden group transition duration-300 uppercase hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-red-600/50 hover:bg-red-600"
          >
            <span class="flex items-center gap-2 button-text text-sm relative z-10 w-full text-center uppercase"
              >Read more about me<svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-width="1.5"
                stroke="currentColor"
                class="size-4"
              >
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5 21 12m0 0-7.5 7.5M21 12H3"></path>
              </svg>
            </span>
            <span
              class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-600 to-red-800 transition-all duration-500 ease-in-out translate-x-full group-hover:translate-x-0"
            ></span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex justify-center lg:w-1/2 mt-8 lg:mt-0">
        <img src="images/pfp.webp" alt="About Me Image" class="w-48 h-48 md:w-[350px] md:h-[350px] rounded-full shadow-md object-cover" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Values Section -->
  <div id="values" class="pt-12 md:pt-20 py-12 px-6">
    <section class="container max-w-screen-xl mx-auto py-6 px-4 md:px-10">
      <div class="bg-gray-700 bg-opacity-80 p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#fafafa] text-center md:text-left">Values & mission</h3>
        <p class="values-text mt-2 mb-12 text-gray-300 leading-7 text-center md:text-left">
          My journey in design is guided by principles of accessibility, creativity, and inclusivity, <br /> ensuring every user has an exceptional experience.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-4 md:space-y-8">
          <!-- Value Item 1 -->
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold mt-1">1</div>
            <div class="ml-10 max-w-xs mx-auto md:max-w-full">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#fafafa]">Accessibility first</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-300 md:text-lg text-md">
                I believe in designing for everyone, <br class="md:hidden block" />creating experiences that are <br class="md:hidden block" /> accessible
                to all users, regardless of ability.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Value Item 2 -->
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold mt-1">2</div>
            <div class="ml-10 max-w-xs mx-auto md:max-w-full">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#fafafa]">User-centered design</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-300 md:text-lg text-md">
                My goal is to create intuitive,<br class="md:hidden block" /> user-friendly interfaces that resonate <br class="md:hidden block" /> with
                users and serve their needs.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Value Item 3 -->
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold mt-1">3</div>
            <div class="ml-10 max-w-xs mx-auto md:max-w-full">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#fafafa]">Continuous growth</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-300 md:text-lg text-md">
                I am committed to learning <br class="md:hidden block" /> and evolving with new design trends <br class="md:hidden block" /> and technologies
                to push boundaries<br class="md:hidden block" /> in digital experiences.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <!-- Skills Section -->
  <div id="skills" class="pt-8 md:pt-20 py-4 px-6">
    <section id="skills" class="container max-w-screen-lg mx-auto py-6 px-4">
      <div class="bg-gray-800 bg-opacity-70 p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#fafafa] text-center md:text-left">Skills & tools</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 mb-12 text-gray-300 leading-7 text-center md:text-left">
          Here’s a quick overview of my skills, tools, and technologies that <br /> I use to bring digital experiences to life.
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mt-8">
          <!-- Skill Item -->
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">H</div>
            <p class="ml-4 text-gray-300">HTML & CSS</p>
          </div>
          <!-- Skill Item -->
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">JS</div>
            <p class="ml-4 text-gray-300">JavaScript & frameworks</p>
          </div>
          <!-- Skill Item -->
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">UX</div>
            <p class="ml-4 text-gray-300">UX & UI Design</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Skill Item(s) -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mt-8">
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">F</div>
            <p class="ml-4 text-gray-300">Figma & Canva</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">P</div>
            <p class="ml-4 text-gray-300">Photoshop & Illustrator</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">Git</div>
            <p class="ml-4 text-gray-300">Git & GitHub</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
  <!-- Workflow Section -->
  <div id="workflow">
    <section id="workflow-section" class="container max-w-screen-lg mx-auto py-6 px-4">
      <div class="bg-gray-700 bg-opacity-80 p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#fafafa] text-center md:text-left">Process & workflow</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 mb-12 text-gray-300 leading-7 text-center md:text-left">
          I follow a structured process to ensure every project meets its full <br /> potential, from concept to final design.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-8">
          <!-- Workflow Step 1 -->
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">1</div>
            <div class="ml-4 max-w-xs mx-auto md:max-w-full">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#fafafa]">Planning & strategy</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-300 md:text-lg text-md">Creating a to-do list to get an overview of the project and what needs to be done.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Workflow Step 2 -->
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">2</div>
            <div class="ml-4 max-w-xs mx-auto md:max-w-full">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#fafafa]">Research & discovery</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-300 md:text-lg text-md">
                Understanding the project-goals, <br class="md:hidden block" /> audience, and challenges.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Workflow Step 3 -->
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">3</div>
            <div class="ml-4 max-w-xs mx-auto md:max-w-full">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#fafafa]">Design & development</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-300 md:text-lg text-md">
                Creating wireframes, prototypes, <br class="md:hidden block" /> and final design-elements.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Workflow Step 4 -->
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">4</div>
            <div class="ml-4 max-w-xs mx-auto md:max-w-full">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#fafafa]">Coding & testing</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-300 md:text-lg text-md">Building the project from the ground up.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Workflow Step 5 -->
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">5</div>
            <div class="ml-4 max-w-xs mx-auto md:max-w-full">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#fafafa]">Final testing & feedback</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-300 md:text-lg text-md">
                Gathering feedback and refining to <br class="md:hidden block" /> achieve the best user-experience.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Workflow Step 6 -->
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-site-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-[#fafafa] font-bold">6</div>
            <div class="ml-4 max-w-xs mx-auto md:max-w-full">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#fafafa]">Deployment</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-300 md:text-lg text-md">Deploying the project to production.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
  <!-- Projects Section -->
  <div id="projects" class="md:pt-20 py-12 px-6">
    <section id="project-section" class="container max-w-screen-xl mx-auto py-6 px-4 bg-gray-800 bg-opacity-70 rounded-lg shadow-lg mt-8">
      <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold max-w-4xl mx-auto text-[#fafafa] md:text-left text-center pt-10">Highlighted projects</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 mb-10 text-gray-300 leading-7 max-w-4xl mx-auto md:text-left text-center md:text-lg text-base">
        I have worked on a lot of different projects in the past, each different in its own way. However, some of them are not as important as others.
        When taking this sort of course, you're bound to have both favorite and least favorite projects. Because you can't always decide what kind of
        project you have to do. I've decided to highlight some of the projects that I'm most proud of.
      </p>

      <div id="projects-grid" class="flex flex-col items-start max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-4 mb-8">
        <div class="w-full md:text-left text-center">
          <em class="text-gray-400 text-lg">Click on the boxes corresponding to each project to see more.</em>
        </div>

        <!-- Button Container -->
        <div class="flex md:justify-start justify-center w-full">
          <a
            href="/other"
            class="project-button relative z-10 text-[#fafafa] bg-site-red font-bold rounded-lg text-sm px-6 py-3 inline-flex overflow-hidden group transition duration-300 uppercase hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-red-600/50 hover:bg-red-600"
          >
            <span class="flex items-center gap-2 button-text text-sm relative z-10 w-full text-center uppercase"
              >Or see other projects <svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-width="1.5"
                stroke="currentColor"
                class="size-4"
              >
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5 21 12m0 0-7.5 7.5M21 12H3"></path>
              </svg>
            </span>
            <span
              class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-red-600 to-red-800 transition-all duration-500 ease-in-out translate-x-full group-hover:translate-x-0"
            ></span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Carousel -->

      <div class="min-h-[350px] relative">
        <div class="container mx-auto w-full overflow-hidden relative">
          <div class="w-full h-full absolute">
            <div class="w-1/4 h-full absolute z-30 left-0" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, rgb(22, 31, 42), rgba(22, 31, 42, 0));"></div>
            <div class="w-1/4 h-full absolute z-30 right-0" style="background: linear-gradient(to left, rgb(31, 41, 55), rgba(22, 31, 42, 0));"></div>
          </div>

          <div id="logo-slider" class="logo-slider overflow-hidden">
            <div class="marquee">
              <div
                class="carousel-items flex items-center justify-center"
                style="width: fit-content; animation: carouselAnim 10s infinite alternate linear;"
              >
                <!-- Carousel Item 1 -->
                <a
                  href="https://sararingkow.dk/kea/02_web/01_website/website/index.html"
                  target="_blank"
                  class="carousel-focus flex items-center flex-col relative bg-gray-700 mx-5 my-10 px-4 py-3 rounded-lg shadow-lg hover:bg-gray-600 transition duration-300"
                  style="width: 400px;"
                  aria-label="View project: Entrance exam (1st semester)"
                >
                  <span class="text-[#fafafa] font-bold mb-3 p-2 md:text-left text-center">Entrance exam <br /> (1st semester project)</span>
                  <img
                    class="h-[150px] w-[150px] rounded-full shadow-2xl object-cover aspect-[1/1] flex-shrink-0"
                    src="images/entrance_exam.webp"
                    alt="Screenshot of entrance-exam (frontpage)"
                  />
                  <p class="mt-3 md:text-left text-center leading-7 p-4 text-gray-300">
                    This project was my very first project, created as part of the entrance-exam to the multimedia-design course. It's a site that
                    revolves around computers. We had to make this to show what we had learned during the first three weeks of the course.
                  </p>
                </a>

                <!-- Carousel Item 2 -->
                <a
                  href="http://sararingkow.dk/kea/03_ux/01_kodet_site/index.html"
                  target="_blank"
                  class="carousel-focus flex items-center flex-col relative bg-gray-700 mx-5 my-10 px-4 py-3 rounded-lg shadow-lg hover:bg-gray-600 transition duration-300"
                  style="width: 400px;"
                  aria-label="View project: UX/UI-site (1st semester project)"
                >
                  <span class="text-[#fafafa] font-bold mb-3 p-2 md:text-left text-center">UX/UI-site <br /> (1st semester project)</span>
                  <img
                    class="h-[150px] w-[150px] rounded-full shadow-2xl object-cover aspect-[1/1] flex-shrink-0"
                    src="images/ux_site.webp"
                    alt="Screenshot of UX/UI-site (frontpage)"
                  />
                  <p class="mt-3 md:text-left text-center leading-7 p-4 text-gray-300">
                    This was our first real project after the entrance-exam. Here, we had to create a site that revolved around a topic of our own
                    choice. Since I'm a huge fan of almost everything that spells Nintendo and Super Mario, I chose to create a sort of Super Mario
                    wikipedia-site.
                  </p>
                </a>

                <!-- Carousel Item 3 -->
                <a
                  href="https://makomiteen.netlify.app/"
                  target="_blank"
                  class="carousel-focus flex items-center flex-col relative bg-gray-700 mx-5 my-10 px-4 py-3 rounded-lg shadow-lg hover:bg-gray-600 transition duration-300"
                  style="width: 400px;"
                  aria-label="View project: The MAK committee (1st semester case-project)"
                >
                  <span class="text-[#fafafa] font-bold mb-3 p-2 md:text-left text-center">The MAK committee <br /> (1st semester case-project)</span>
                  <img
                    class="h-[150px] w-[150px] rounded-full shadow-2xl object-cover aspect-[1/1] flex-shrink-0"
                    src="images/mak.webp"
                    alt="Screenshot of the MAK committee (frontpage)"
                  />
                  <p class="mt-3 md:text-left text-center leading-7 p-4 text-gray-300">
                    This was the very first case-project. We had to redesign a website for a business of our own choice. We chose the non-global
                    organisation MAK <em>(the central-America committee)</em>, that a former classmate of mine was/is volunteering for.
                  </p>
                </a>

                <!-- Carousel Item 4 -->
                <a
                  href="https://sararingkow.dk/kea/06_eksamen/portfolio_eksamen/index.html"
                  target="_blank"
                  class="carousel-focus flex items-center flex-col relative bg-gray-700 mx-5 my-10 px-4 py-3 rounded-lg shadow-lg hover:bg-gray-600 transition duration-300"
                  style="width: 400px;"
                  aria-label="View project: Portfolio-site (1st semester exam-project)"
                >
                  <span class="text-[#fafafa] font-bold mb-3 p-2 md:text-left text-center">Portfolio-site <br /> (1st semester exam-project)</span>
                  <img
                    class="h-[150px] w-[150px] rounded-full shadow-2xl object-cover aspect-[1/1] flex-shrink-0"
                    src="images/1st_portfolio.webp"
                    alt="Screenshot of 1st portfolio (frontpage)"
                  />
                  <p class="mt-3 md:text-left text-center leading-7 p-4 text-gray-300">
                    This was the first portfolio-site that I made, which was made as part of my 1st semester exam. Here, we had to make our own
                    portfolio, completely from scratch. Though I'm not particularly fond of it, I still included it here because of its importance.
                  </p>
                </a>

                <!-- Carousel Item 5 -->
                <a
                  href="https://t8-karrusel.netlify.app/"
                  target="_blank"
                  class="carousel-focus flex items-center flex-col relative bg-gray-700 mx-5 my-10 px-4 py-3 rounded-lg shadow-lg hover:bg-gray-600 transition duration-300"
                  style="width: 400px;"
                  aria-label="View project: Karrusel Festival (2nd semester case-project)"
                >
                  <span class="text-[#fafafa] font-bold mb-3 p-2 md:text-left text-center">Karrusel Festival <br />(2nd semester case-project)</span>
                  <img
                    class="h-[150px] w-[150px] rounded-full shadow-2xl object-cover aspect-[1/1] flex-shrink-0"
                    src="images/karrusel.webp"
                    alt="Screenshot of Karrusel Festival (frontpage)"
                  />
                  <p class="mt-3 md:text-left text-center leading-7 p-4 text-gray-300">
                    This was the second case-project on 2nd semester. Here, we had to redesign a website for a rave-festival called Karrusel. This
                    might be one among the best projects I've made during my studies.
                  </p>
                </a>

                <!-- Carousel Item 6 -->
                <a
                  href="https://itmv-t9.netlify.app/"
                  target="_blank"
                  class="carousel-focus flex items-center flex-col relative bg-gray-700 mx-5 my-10 px-4 py-3 rounded-lg shadow-lg hover:bg-gray-600 transition duration-300"
                  style="width: 400px;"
                  aria-label="View project: I Tråd Med Verden (2nd semester case-project)"
                >
                  <span class="text-[#fafafa] font-bold mb-3 p-2 md:text-left text-center">I Tråd Med Verden <br />(2nd semester case-project)</span>
                  <img
                    class="h-[150px] w-[150px] rounded-full shadow-2xl object-cover aspect-[1/1] flex-shrink-0"
                    src="images/itmv.webp"
                    alt="Screenshot of I Tråd Med Verden (frontpage)"
                  />
                  <p class="mt-3 md:text-left text-center leading-7 p-4 text-gray-300">
